Former New York City Mayor Michael Bloomberg is on track to have spent nearly $5 million of his vast fortune on each delegate he won on Super Tuesday, according to a Daily Caller News Foundation analysis.
Biden is projected to win 670 delegates, The NYT projects, meaning he has spent $23,881 on each of his delegates thus far.
Bloomberg’s campaign dumped more than $234 million into TV, radio and digital ads in the Super Tuesday states.
(RELATED: Sanders, Biden, Bloomberg Have Paid Combined $466,000 To Superdelegates)“The biggest loser tonight, by far, is Mini Mike Bloomberg.
Bloomberg told reporters in November 2019 that he plans on spending $500 million or more to defeat President Donald Trump.